The North America and Europe regions are the major contributors to the medical Raman probe market, due to the presence of advanced healthcare infrastructure and high adoption of innovative medical technologies.

5. What are the challenges faced by the medical Raman probe market?
High cost of Raman spectroscopy systems and lack of skilled professionals in the field of Raman spectroscopy are the major challenges faced by the medical Raman probe market.

6. What are the potential opportunities in the medical Raman probe market?
The integration of Raman spectroscopy with other imaging technologies and expanding applications in pharmaceutical and biotechnology industries are the potential opportunities in the medical Raman probe market.

